Component 5: The Incompetent Officials
Jarl Korir (Winterhold): Trusts the party completely because they reported success. His flaw is desperation — he cannot afford panic and is actively suppressing information that might cause his last survivors to flee. He will not doubt the party until confronted with evidence he cannot dismiss. Then he will be devastated.
Arch-Mage Savos Aren (College of Winterhold): Not lying maliciously. He genuinely believes his experiments are stabilizing the cold. His flaw is that he has been studying the Eye of Magnus for years and its influence has subtly warped his priorities. He wants to help. He also, without knowing it, wants the Eye more than he wants to admit. His advice is slightly off in ways that only become clear in retrospect.
Jarl Ulfric Stormcloak (Windhelm): Not a villain here. Not relevant to the plot. Sees the spreading cold as a harsh Skyrim winter. Is focused entirely on the Civil War. Will not engage with the party's concerns unless they have proof he cannot politically ignore. Represents the world going on around this crisis as if it isn't happening.

Part Two: Ismara Ice-Born
Everything in this campaign flows through Ismara. Understanding her completely is the GM's most important preparation task. She is not a monster. She is not a victim. She is an apex intelligence operating according to a coherent internal logic that the party will spend five adventures trying to understand.
History & Context
Ismara Ice-Born was a Nordic sorceress operating in the era before the Dragon War. She and Hjolmar Ice-Shaper pioneered cognitive matrix technology — the theoretical and practical framework for crystallizing a living mind in a stable magical substrate. Her contribution was the permafrost ice matrix. It allows her mind to continue learning, adapting, updating. This is her greatest strength and her most meaningful vulnerability.
She made a pact with the Dragon Cult, offering her research in exchange for power to protect her people during the Dragon War. When the nature of the Cult's actual objectives became clear to her, she attempted to defect and work against them. She was captured and imprisoned at Frostmere Barrow. The sealing ritual used her own crown's architecture against her, creating a resonance trap that made it impossible for her to break free without destroying herself.
She has been frozen in that throne room for approximately 4,000 years. Fully conscious. Fully aware. Unable to move, speak, or act. The party freed her.
GM NOTE: Four thousand years of conscious immobility has not broken her. It has refined her. Every redundant thought has been discarded. Every emotional response has been examined and filed. She is not traumatized in any recognizable sense. She is crystallized. She came out of that prison more herself than she went in.
