What Is Actually Happening:
This is the first city Ismara has seen in four thousand years. Windhelm is built over Atmoran foundations she recognizes — the street geometry partially follows old survey lines. The catacombs beneath the city contain pre-Nordic construction that gives her geographic anchors she needs to calibrate her ritual calculations for the full Skyrim network.
She needs three things from Windhelm: to survey the Atmoran foundations, to establish her initial geometric coordinates, and to place her first nodes. She knows the Khajiit needs a healer and uses this as her stated reason for coming here. She says: Windhelm has healers. And I need to see the city.
Getting In: The gates are guarded. Ismara is visibly not a living person. This is the party's problem to solve. Do not solve it for them.
Key Locations:
The Hall of the Dead: Helgrid the priest is helpful if approached. The catacombs below are old. Ismara knows exactly where she is going in the lower levels.
The Palace of the Kings — Wulfgar the Scholar: Elderly Atmoran linguist, ignored by Ulfric's court. Can partially translate the rune notation as "structural — architectural marks for large-scale magical engineering." A thread, not an answer.
The Gray Quarter: Where Ismara can move most freely in a city that would kill her on sight. The Dunmer population's outsider status provides cover.
The Catacombs: Pre-Nordic construction. Evidence of an earlier, failed attempt at the same ritual — seven frozen figures, ancient, standing in precise positions. The geometry of those figures, mapped against current events, uses the same spatial logic.
The Namira Thread: In the deepest sealed section of the catacombs, a body that has not decomposed. Peaceful. Hands folded. A symbol in the floor that is neither Nordic nor Atmoran. The Orc feels at home here. Develop based on what the player does.
Suvaris Atheron: A Dunmer beggar in the Gray Quarter who has been eating the flesh of one of the frozen. She says: "It tastes like winter. Like something very old. I can hear it thinking, a little, when I do it. Not words. Just... presence." She is a Namira thread, not a plot point.
Ismara's Action: She places her first nodes. A dockworker. A laborer. If the party sees it and asks: This one is necessary. If pressed: All of them are.
Ending: The party leaves Windhelm with a partial map of node positions, knowledge that this has been attempted before, and a managed (not cured) rotjoint. Ismara tells them she wants to head west. She says she needs to understand the political landscape. This is true. It is also not the full reason.

